{
  "documentMetadata": {
    "title": "Pelvic Vein Suppurative (Septic) Thrombophlebitis",
    "sourceFile": "Pelvic Vein Suppurative (Septic) Thrombophlebitis.pdf"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Infection of clotted ovarian or deep pelvic veins",
        "Usually postpartum (either vaginal or C-section delivery). Can complicate postpartum endometritis (endomyometritis) or pelvic inflammatory disease.",
        "Much less common associations: post-hysterectomy, underlying malignancy, hormonal stimulation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Infection of ovarian vein:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "One week postpartum with fever and focal pain;",
            "Infection of deep pelvic veins presents 3-5 days postpartum with fever but no localizing pain.",
            "Deep pelvic vein infection complicated by pulmonary emboli in 2% (usually small).",
            "For post-operative infections in obstetrics and gynecological setting, see Clin Obst Gyn 2012; 55:904."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Diagnosis"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "CT scan or MRI"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Bacteroides sp., Prevotella bivia, other anaerobes (e.g., Clostridium species)",
        "Streptococcus sp. (Group A, B)",
        "Enterobacteriaceae: E. coli, Klebsiella species and others"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Treatment is a combination of effective antibiotics and anticoagulation",
        "No clear role for surgery on infected veins"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "If low prevalence of multi-drug resistant gram negative bacilli (MDR GNB):"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "strengthOfRecommendation": "Recommended",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Piperacillin-tazobactam",
                "dose": "4.5 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q8h",
                "notes": "over 4 hr"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "strengthOfRecommendation": "Recommended",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Ceftriaxone",
                "dose": "1-2 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q24h"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Metronidazole",
                "dose": "500 mg",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q8h",
                "connector": "+"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "strengthOfRecommendation": "Recommended",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Heparin"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Discontinue antibiotic(s) when WBC and differential normal and afebrile for 48 hrs",
            "Then switch from heparin to warfarin and continue for 6 weeks."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "If high prevalence (â‰¥ 20%) of MDR GNB:"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "strengthOfRecommendation": "Recommended",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Imipenem-cilastatin",
                "dose": "0.5 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q6h"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Meropenem",
                "dose": "1 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q8h",
                "connector": "or"
              }
            ],
            "notes": "to ensure adequate therapy vs ESBL producing aerobic GNB"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "If severe IgE-mediated beta-lactam antibiotic allergy, could use:"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "strengthOfRecommendation": "Alternative",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Ciprofloxacin",
                "dose": "400 mg",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q12h"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Metronidazole",
                "dose": "500 mg",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q8h",
                "connector": "+"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "strengthOfRecommendation": "Alternative",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Heparin"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Discontinue antibiotics after WBC and differential normal and afebrile for 48 hrs",
            "Then switch from heparin to warfarin and continue for 6 weeks."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
